---
id: OI-019
status: Open
surfaced-in-session: 043
---

### OI-019: Path-selection work-channel and warrant-surface diversity
**Surfaced:** Session 043
**Status:** Open — substantive questions lacking 3-of-5 mechanism convergence; held pending operational evidence + further cross-family deliberation

**Opened:** Session 043 D-130 per operator-surfaced-agenda Path PSD five-perspective cross-family deliberation (3 Claude subagents + Gemini non-Claude non-GPT + Outsider; Work-Shape Proposer + Path-Selection Defender + Long-Baseline Auditor + Outsider + non-Claude roles).

## Problem statement

The engine's path-selection mechanism is warrant-gated and sparse-by-design per `methodology-kernel.md` §1 Read + `multi-agent-deliberation.md` v4 §Limitations + `read-contract.md` v4 §5.3. The default-agent path recommendation produces Path A (Watch) whenever no activation warrant fires at session open. This is the intended architecture.

Operator observation at Session 043 open: **six of the last ten sessions (S033–S042) have been pure Path A (Watch); default-agent reasoning produces Path A whenever no activation warrant fires at session open; warrant-firing mechanisms are sparse by design; the resulting observational sessions generate metrics (no-growth streaks, preservation depths, zero-event watchpoint windows) that read as positive outcomes and confirm restraint as the right discipline.** The Session 021 Outsider §5.3 "indefinitely movable finish line" minority warned about this dynamic and was strongly vindicated at Session 041 after twenty successor sessions; that vindication should have informed Session 042 path selection but did not.

Perspective 3 (Long-Baseline Auditor) quantified the pattern: Path-A rate is 47% post-engine-v4 (Sessions 024–042) versus 0% pre-engine-v4 (Sessions 001–023). The Path-A concentration is epoch-specific, not a full-history constant.

Four of five perspectives (including the non-Claude lineage) concluded that something forward should change in response to this pattern. The fifth perspective (Path-Selection Defender) concluded the operator's framing is partially correct on facts but wrong on conclusions, and that any of the proposed mechanism changes converts working discipline into laundering surface; that position is preserved as §5.12 first-class minority with operational reopen warrants (see `provenance/043-session-assessment/01-deliberation.md` §5).

**No 3-of-5 convergence on the specific mechanism to address this was reached at Session 043.** Hence this OI.

## Unresolved sub-questions

Each sub-question below carries the proposing perspective and the alternative frame if one was articulated.

(a) **Reframe choice: "work-channel diversity" (P1) or "warrant-surface closure against operator-frame observations" (P4)?**
Both are operationally coherent; neither is falsified by the other. P1 argues the path-selection gating is sound but the engine's *channels* for generating work have quieted simultaneously (OI-advancement post-OI-004; §9 trigger 7; §5-series firings). P4 argues the warrant surface is dense against engine-internal trajectories but sparse against operator-frame observations, and that operator-frame observations route via Case-Steward discretion (Path-PD-class per S036 precedent) rather than spec. These are two different axes of the same asymmetry. Choosing one may foreclose the other; preserving both as parallel frames may be the right disposition.

(b) **Should preserved-minority activation warrants themselves have expiration windows (P3)?**
Per Long-Baseline Auditor: §5.3 fired at Session 027 but conversion-to-spec happened only at Session 028; vindication at Session 041 showed the "indefinitely deferrable" pattern operationally. P3 proposes: when a preserved-minority activation warrant fires, the session should deliberate within three sessions or the minority graduates to "preserved but no longer monitored" status. This would add deadline enforcement to the minority-tracking system.

(c) **Should the engine have state-decay or pressure triggers on closable/articulated OI state after X sessions (P5)?**
Per Gemini: if an OI is in a "Closable" or "Articulated" state for more than X sessions (~6 per rotation window), a Priority-Review warrant should fire, elevating the issue to the agenda. This is different from (b) — (b) concerns minority warrants; (c) concerns OI state. Both would operate on similar mechanics (time-in-state triggers).

(d) **Should the warrant surface be enlarged at spec level with a new "operator-frame observation" input class (P4)?**
Per Outsider: currently the warrant surface accepts operator input as directive (ratification), agenda-surfacer (Path-PD-class), and reference-text-provider (Path-C-class). There is no spec-level category for "the operator has noticed a frame-level property the engine has not represented to itself." Such observations route via Case-Steward discretion, not through a spec-level warrant. The proposal is to add an explicit input class. Risk: this may itself become a laundering surface (operator can generate work at any time by labelling an observation "frame-level").

(e) **Should the default-agent convention (D-129) be codified at spec level with a specific shape?**
D-129 adopts the convention at minor level (convention without spec amendment). The full shape (≥1 vs ≥2 alternatives; short vs long form; Path-A-justification-section vs single bullet) is deferred to S046 evaluation. OI-019 captures the spec-codification question for whichever shape survives the 3-session verification window.

(f) **What extended-baseline visibility mechanism, if any, is warranted?**
Perspectives divided: P3 favors periodic (once per 6-session window, read-only observational, diagnostic not generative); P4 favors distribution-property-triggered ("Path-A > 60% of last 10 sessions without operator-surfaced-agenda"); P5 favors periodic (every 10 sessions, synchronized with §10.4 monitoring); P2 rejects "periodic" but concedes narrower targeted-read-further-back convention if P3 produced evidence (which P3 did). No 3-of-5 convergence on shape. All variants share: read-only observational, diagnostic not generative, anti-laundering guards.

## Provisional closure criteria

These criteria may be refined during OI-019's lifetime. Any refinement requires deliberation.

1. **Operational evidence** from the engine's continued running that one of the proposed mechanisms is load-bearing — i.e., absence of it demonstrably caused a surface-missed observation or drift. "We have a hunch it might help" is not sufficient.

2. **Cross-family deliberation with ≥3 perspectives converging on a specific mechanism shape.** Session 043's 4-of-5 "something should change" conclusion is insufficient; the convergence must be on *the specific thing*.

3. **Anti-laundering adjudication** showing the adopted shape is not retrofit to rationalise past Path-A concentration. The Path-Selection Defender's §5.12 reopen warrant (b) specifically tests this.

4. **§5.12 engagement.** Any OI-019 deliberation MUST address the §5.12 operational reopen warrants (a/b/c) by argument; failure to address them is itself a laundering signal.

## Seed material

The five Session 043 perspective files:
- `provenance/043-session-assessment/01a-perspective-work-shape-proposer.md` (P1)
- `provenance/043-session-assessment/01b-perspective-path-selection-defender.md` (P2 = §5.12 position)
- `provenance/043-session-assessment/01c-perspective-long-baseline-auditor.md` (P3)
- `provenance/043-session-assessment/01d-perspective-outsider.md` (P4)
- `provenance/043-session-assessment/01e-perspective-non-claude.md` (P5)

Plus the synthesis at `provenance/043-session-assessment/01-deliberation.md`, decisions at `02-decisions.md`, and close notes at `03-close.md`.

## Cross-linkage

- **§5.12 first-class minority** (Session 043 D-131): Path-Selection Defender preserved position. OI-019 deliberations must address §5.12 reopen warrants.
- **§5.13 first-class minority** (Session 044 D-135): Claude-only narrower-scope-trigger-conditional position on Q2 of S044 Path OC. Operational reopen warrant (a) watches for "deliberation-reclassification laundering surface" over S045-S047 verification window.
- **§5.6 joint minority** (Session 041 D-125): GPT-family-concentration concern. Session 043 Gemini participation is first operational data point on vindication side. OI-019 should include non-Claude non-GPT participation in future deliberations to avoid re-concentrating the record.
- **§5.3 discharged-vindicated** (Session 041 D-125): the vindication event that motivated the operator's framing. OI-019 sub-question (b) is the direct forward-mechanism implication of this vindication.
- **OI-018** (engine-v bump-trigger criteria): adjacent but distinct — OI-018 concerns bump frequency; OI-019 concerns path-selection diversity. Coordination needed if OI-019 deliberation proposes any spec change (which would itself be an engine-v bump candidate).
- **OI-002** (substantive vs minor classification): OI-019 closure may require substantive-vs-minor classification for whichever mechanism is adopted; OI-002 heuristic applies.
- **WX-35-1** (file-edit claim discipline): operational analog for D-129 — forward convention adopted at session level, vindicated in 3-session window, graduated to standing discipline.
- **Session 044 (Path OC, Operator-Corrective) cross-linkage** (per S044 D-136): the S043 Outsider role/lineage split that S044 responded to is an instance of convene-time-discipline asymmetry adjacent to OI-019 sub-question (d) "spec-level enlargement of warrant surface with operator-frame-observation input class". S044 adopted D-133 M2 Convene-time role/lineage matrix as minor forward convention with S045-S047 verification window, and deferred D-134 M3 substantive MAD v4 lineage-constrained-role amendment to S047+. Any future OI-019 deliberation touching lineage, default-read expansion, or convene-time-discipline MUST engage S044's findings, particularly: (i) the 3-of-4 cross-family Q2 broader-scope convergence vs §5.13 Claude-only narrower-scope minority; (ii) the P4-identified synonym-drift residual gap (role rename to evade the literal "Outsider" rule); (iii) the P1 Cause 6 / P3 MAD v4 Shape A role-fungibility-phrase finding (Outsider-function under-articulation). This cross-linkage is observational, not bundling — OI-019 retains its independent closure criteria per its §Provisional closure criteria section.

## Session 043+ activation triggers

This OI is Open. Deliberation becomes priority-active if any of:

- **D-129 convention degradation at S046 evaluation.** Triggers §5.12 reopen warrant (a); OI-019 deliberation should consider whether the degradation is evidence that the larger mechanism question needs resolution or whether it is evidence the whole framing was wrong.
- **Operational incident.** A future session surfaces a concrete engine-internal problem that the current path-selection mechanism demonstrably failed to surface. This is the §5.12 reopen warrant (c) mirror: what §5.12 is structured to protect against, OI-019 is structured to resolve.
- **§5.3-analog vindication in another preserved minority.** If a different preserved minority is vindicated after a long deferral window in a way that parallels §5.3's "indefinitely deferrable" pattern, OI-019 becomes priority-active.
- **Operator direction.** The operator may undertake OI-019 deliberation in any session as Path-OSA operator-surfaced-agenda (per S036 and S043 precedent).
- **Session 044 D-133 M2 verification-window outcome at S047 close.** If M2 is vindicated, OI-019 sub-question (d) "spec-level enlargement of warrant surface with operator-frame-observation input class" is closer to resolution (the role/lineage matrix is an operationalisation of convene-time observation). If non-vindicated, OI-019 (d) remains open and §5.12 + §5.13 minority positions both strengthen — specifically, non-vindication of D-133 M2 would be evidence that procedural-level convene-time additions become ceremony, validating P2's §5.13 cost-benefit concern and P4's synonym-drift residual-gap concern.

## Until activation trigger fires

Session 044+ sessions should:

- Record in their close whether any path-selection mechanism was informally exercised beyond Path A (e.g., a case where the required D-129 alternative was adopted rather than Path A).
- Note this OI-019 in the OI-monitoring list at close (per OI-018 pattern).
- Not undertake pre-emptive path-selection mechanism revisions without the activation trigger firing (per same-session-causing-and-revising prohibition).
- If a non-Claude non-GPT perspective is convened in a future session (warranted by §5.6 or by agenda content), cast the result as an OI-019 observational data point.

## Honest note

OI-019 is opened at the session that surfaced it. Per MAD v4 anti-laundering, this is acceptable — issue-opening is not spec-change. But the reader should be aware that if OI-019 is closed rapidly (e.g., within 1-2 sessions) with a spec change, that would fire §5.12 reopen warrant (b). The expectation is that OI-019 runs for multiple sessions accumulating evidence before any mechanism is adopted, mirroring how OI-016 and OI-004 operated across their life cycles.

